refactor: migrate from Odoo to external PIM API

Replace Odoo XML-RPC based PIM integration with a new external REST API
using Bearer token authentication.

Changes:
- Add pimClient.ts with HTTP client for external PIM API
- Add externalPim.ts adapter matching odooPim interface
- Update 3rdparty/pim route to use new adapter
- Rewrite sync.ts to pull from external PIM API and index to Solr
- Remove Odoo client, adapter, and test script
- Remove @foxglove/xmlrpc dependency
- Update .env.template with new PIM_URL and PIM_TOKEN variables
- Update CLAUDE.md documentation
- Use /api/v1/* endpoints instead of /api/public/* (per updated spec)
- Explicitly filter for published products in all PIM queries
- Update types to match latest OpenAPI spec:
  - Add ProductListItem for list responses
  - Add Product with categories/classifications for detail responses
  - Add ProductCategoryAssociation and ProductClassificationAssociation types
  - Remove timestamps from ProductAttribute type
- Add category fetching to sync script:
  - Pull categories from PIM API before products
  - Display category hierarchy with product counts
  - Build category map for future category-product association
